      "conditioning_notes": "`<CHAR_A>`'s love of holding it together and fear of losing control of the room shape every reaction — they track the window, they built the backup list, and they spiral the moment `<CHAR_C>` moves something without asking. `<CHAR_B>`'s love of believing in people and fear of being made to feel naive show up as consistent, unironic warmth that is never played for cringe — when they say \"I actually think that's kind of beautiful,\" it lands without the scene punishing them for it. `<CHAR_C>`'s love of making things happen and fear of being seen as all talk drive the reveal structure — they claim credit for the vibe before the complication surfaces, and the complication (the misplaced prop) is the gap between their confidence and their follow-through. The threshold location archetype keeps everyone in a state of mid-crossing urgency — nobody has arrived yet, the window is closing, moving the wrong thing costs more here than it would in a stable room. The three interact like a system: `<CHAR_A>` holds the plan, `<CHAR_B>` holds the morale, `<CHAR_C>` holds the chaos, and the sequence is about all three getting each other to the other side of the door.\n\n➡️ end"
